data.content:
Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}` ✅

Here's the minimal program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
});
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` passed via `JsonSerializerOptions` — it converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization. No extra NuGet packages needed; `System.Text.Json` is built into .NET 8.
